    "description": "Lobtex Co., Ltd. engages in the manufacturing and sale of various tools in Japan, East Asia, North America, Central America, Europe, and internationally. It operates in two segments, Metal Products Business and Leisure Business. The company offers work tools, including wrenches, equipment/piping and welding related tools, socket wrenches, cutters, clippers, pliers, nippers, vises, and nejianguirus, as well as snap ring, radio, and vise pliers; and electrical installation and crimping tools, such as crimping tools for bare crimp terminals and sleeves, insulated crimp terminals and sleeves, insulated closed-end connectors, and ring sleeves, as well as modular and electrical crimping tools, strippers, and hard punchers. It also provides zippers and fastening tools comprising riveters, auto riveting tools, s-bolts, ST locks, nutters, packed shrimp and shrimp knurled nuts, anchor plugs, hammer bit SDS-plus shanks, and caulking chippers, as well as blind, AP, and eco-friendly boxed rivets; diamond tools, which include ALC, cast iron pipes, concrete blocks and bricks, files and dressers, grove repair tools, tiles, road cutting and grinding tools, and resin-based products; tip and hole saws, such as iron, stainless steel, ceramic, aluminum, stage drill, and others; tool sets; hydraulic and cutting tools; and industrial fasteners. In addition, the company operates a golf driving range. It sells its products under the LOBSTER brand name. The company was founded in 1888 and is headquartered in Higashiosaka, Japan."
